cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.RO

Reasoning: The paper deals with computer vision and deep learning techniques for 3D shape representation and recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a Convolutional Deep Belief Network for learning the distribution of 3D shapes, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the construction of a large-scale 3D CAD model dataset, which could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for joint object recognition and shape completion, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of view planning for active object recognition, which could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics).
